   WEATHER (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Lawn-care guys, corn farmers and
even scientists agree that predictions of a drought in Missouri and
Kansas are starting to pale. Recent rains ``have washed away'' the
problem in Missouri, an official says. Kansas is drier but not as
bad as the forecasters projected. By John Dvorak and John
Petterson. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
BUSINESS OFFERINGS
</P>
