Democrats hope to compete ferociously. He is something of a policy
wonk, a nice balance to Bush's celebrated aversion to policy
minutiae. He is beloved among Latino voters, a crucial voting bloc.
And he has star appeal as a scion of one of the most famous
political families. Trouble is that family is named Bush. An
interview with Gov. Jeb Bush of Florida. By Richard L. Berke.
