   &UR; SOUTH LEBANON: THEY MADE A DESERT AND CALLED IT PEACE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; `DANGER!'-MINES-LEBANON-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ABBASIYEH, SOUTH LEBANON _ The lost villages of southern Lebanon
are a disgrace. Some, like Ein Arab, have been used as a target
range for Israel's proxy ``South Lebanon Army'' militia. Others,
like Abbasiyeh, have no memorial. Just a single, slightly rusted
sign shows where the village once stood. ``Danger Mines!'' it says
in English, Hebrew and Arab. The Israelis have withdrawn _ up to a
point _ but the village is dead and the soil is now too dangerous
to tread on. So, what was liberation worth?....By Robert Fisk, The
Independent &QL;
</P>
