<P>
   &UR; DEFIANT SHEBAA FARMERS OF SOUTH LEBANON WON'T SURRENDER &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; `SHEBAA-FARMS'-FLAK-INDEPENDENT-800&AMP;ADD &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SHEBAA, SOUTH LEBANON _ Like everything else in Lebanon, land is
about history. And in the case of the hot, jagged, grey rocks above
Shebaa, it's about occupation and war and annexation and a
half-century-old trail upon which Jews were once smuggled into
mandate Palestine. The ``Shebaa farms'' they call these walls of
stone and windswept trees and unkempt fields. And since they may
yet cause another war in southern Lebanon, it's wise to visit the
little village of Shebaa, where an old man remembers history with
the coldness of a book....By Robert Fisk, The Independent &QL;
</P>
