<P>
   &UR; PSST!...CARE FOR A SOUVENIR HEZBOLLAH KEYCHAIN? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HEZBOLLAH-SOUVENIRS-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEIRUT _ Having a wonderful time _ wish you were here. Which is
more or less the message on the ream of postcards now selling
across Lebanon, courtesy of the Islamic resistance. There are
postcards of ``martyrs'' undertaking their last attack against
Israeli troops and of babies carrying Hezbollah flags against
Israeli bunkers; Hezbollah keychains and car bumper stickers; and
pennants for motorcycles, each carrying the guerrilla army's Arabic
logo with a Kalashnikov rifle forming the ``ll'' in
``Hezbollah.''....By Robert Fisk, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
