   (400 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SREBRENICA: `CLEANSED' OF MUSLIMS, BUT NOT OF SERB HATRED &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SREBRENICA-SCARS-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SREBRENICA, BOSNIA _ ``I will never forget this place,'' said
Tima Mehmedovic, trembling on the verge of hysteria. ``It was where
I saw my husband for the last time.'' Mrs. Mehmedovic, 47, came
Tuesday _ along with nearly 3,000 other Bosnian Muslims, mostly
women _ to a wrecked battery factory on the outskirts of Srebrenica
to mark the fifth anniversary of the worst war crime in Europe
since the Nazi era, and the worst humiliation that United Nations
peacekeepers have suffered....By Raymond Whitaker, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (775 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PATTY _ OR PATSY _ HEARST? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PATTY-HEARST-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ When Patty Hearst made her stunning transformation
from society heiress to urban terrorist in the mid-1970s, she
described her family as ``capitalist pigs'' and urged them to
redistribute their ill-gotten millions to the poor. Now, a society
heiress once again, she is embracing her family with open arms _
just as her guerilla past is rushing to catch up with her....By
Andrew Gumbel, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (475 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WORLD ONCE AGAIN DESCENDS ON SUMMIT SHANGRI-LA, CAMP DAVID &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INSIDE-CAMP-DAVID-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Camp David, once named Shangri-La, was a retreat
for President Franklin Delano Roosevelt from the stifling heat
which blankets Washington in the summer. Presidents ever since have
used it as a vacation home, a place to entertain guests and
occasionally _ as is the case this week with the
Barak-Arafat-Clinton summit _ to bring antagonists together to
talk. For the inhabitants of Thurmont, the nearest town to Camp
David, the flurry of activity on their doorstep is nothing new.
They seem more concerned with the local fire department's annual
carnival....By Andrew Marshall, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for this week's Camp David summit) &QL;
</P>
