<P>
   GENES-CANCER (San Antonio) _ Researchers at the University of
Texas Health Science Center say they have identified a protein that
is activated by a gene known as ATM, and now understand how ATM
communicates with another gene implicated in some inherited forms
of breast cancer. By CINDY TUMIEL.
</P>
<P>
   BIG-TOP (Undated) _ Johnathan Lee Iverson is the new kid under
the Big Top. As the youngest and 31st ringmaster of the Ringling
Bros. and Barnum &AMP; Bailey Circus, the 24-year-old is the darling of
the circus. This Manhattan native is a towering 6-foot-5-inches
with the voice of an operatic tenor. Just as impressive, he's the
first African-American to serve as ringmaster. By DANIEL J. VARGAS.
</P>
<P>
   AIDS-CONFERENCE (Duban, South Africa) _ Former South African
President Nelson Mandela closed the 13th International AIDS
Conference on Friday with the kind of rousing speech and call to
action many had hoped to hear earlier from his successor. By
ULYSSES TORASSA.
</P>
