SITE OF THE WEEK &QL; 
Fandom: An aggregation of sites focused on cult favorites from
Batman to Xena, run by hard-core fans. &QL; 
--Where: www.fandom.com &QL; 
--What's cool: With both ``X-Men'' and the second ``Pokemon'' movie
hitting theaters in the next several days, here's a place to go for
lots of information, collectables and conversation related to those
and other faves. This week, for instance, there was a live Webcast
of the ``X-Men'' premiere, along with lots of information about
action figures, videos, comics, books, games and more for each of
about 20 ``domains.'' &QL; 
--Features: Sites run daily news and features, chat and message
boards, top 10 lists, polls, a calendar of interesting new DVD and
video releases, information on premieres and much else. &QL; 
--You'll like this if: You fall blessedly and barely short of being
obsessive about make-believe action heroes of all sorts of
species. &QL;
