<HEADER>
A2069 &Cx1f; paxxx
r f BC-STATES-AWARDS-PA     07-14 0302
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STATES-AWARDS-PA </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards By Jimmy Chuang States News Service
Washington, July 14 -- Court Reproduction Services Inc. of
Philadelphia won a $54,535 contract from the Government Printing
Office in Washington for photographic, mapping, printing and
publication services.
</P>
<P>
   Imperial Wire and Cable Co. Inc. of Newtown won a $62,980
contract from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for
electric wire and power and distribution equipment.
</P>
<P>
   C&AMP;D Technologies Inc. of Blue Bell won two contracts--one is a
$477,607 contract and the other is a $298,504 contract--from the
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for electric wire
and power and distribution equipment.
</P>
<P>
   J.E. Morgan Knitting Mills Inc. of Tamaqua won a $281,774
contract from the Defense Personnel Support Center in Philadelphia
for clothing, individual equipment and insignia.
</P>
<P>
   SKF Industries Inc. of Kulpsville won a $53,830 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for bearings.
</P>
<P>
   Mine Safety Appliance Co. of Pittsburgh won a $50,407 contract
from the Defense Personnel Support Center in Philadelphia for
firefighting, rescue and safety equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Wheeler Bros Inc. of Somerset won a $261,510 contract from the
U.S. Army Tank-Automotive and Armaments Command in Warren, Mich.,
for valves.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $84,500 contract from
the Defense Industrial Supply Center in Philadelphia for hardware
and abrasives.
</P>
<P>
   K&AMP;J Associates Inc. of Philadelphia won a $117,400 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for electrical
and electronic equipment components.
</P>
<P>
   Stein Seal Co. of Kulpsville won a $74,022 contract from the
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for engines,
turbines and components.
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
