<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cox News Service mistakenly reported Thursday that Sen. Kay
Bailey Hutchison, R-Texas, co-authored a letter to President
Clinton opposing his nomination of El Paso lawyer Enrique Moreno as
a judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 5th Circuit. Hutchison
neither wrote nor signed the letter, which was authored by Sen.
Phil Gramm, R-Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Hutchison does oppose Moreno's nomination, said press secretary
Lisette Mondello, who issued the following statement: ``This
process has approved 17 Clinton judges, while only two have been
turned down, but it was late in the term and the (Judiciary)
committee was not comfortable with an appellate court appointment
for a person who had no judicial experience and no written
record.''
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
