   Bush enjoys an ``enthusiasm edge,'' with a greater proportion of
voters who described themselves as Republicans supporting him than
do Democrats who say they support Gore. Only 47 percent Democrats
said they strongly support Gore, compared with 56 percent of
Republicans who counted themselves as strong supporters of Bush.
</P>
<P>
   Over all, a slim majority of voters, no matter who they support,
said they believe Bush will win the election. Fifty-one percent
predicted that Bush will win, compared to 34 percent who said Gore
and 15 percent who said they do not know.
