N A T I O N A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
WACO &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WACO, Texas _ A five-member advisory jury decided that the
government is not responsible for the deaths of about 80 people at
the Branch Davidians' complex near Waco in 1993. Federal Judge
Walter Smith Jr. will take the recommendation under advisement and
is expected to issue his verdict later this summer, after he hears
arguments on whether the government fired into the complex on April
19. By JENNIFER AUTREY. Story will move in ``a'' general news
category. With sidebars as appropriate, including a short listing
the four questions considered by the jury. &QL; 
 &QL; 
