r l BC-FASHION-CHEAPTHRILLS1     07-14 0469
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FASHION-CHEAPTHRILLS16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Savvy shoppers find fashion bang for the buck at discount chains
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 16.
 &HT;    By Alma E. Hill
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sometimes, it's chic to shop cheap.
</P>
<P>
   Discount chains make it easy for women to buy into fads by
offering less-expensive knockoffs of the season's most popular
styles.
</P>
<P>
   The fashionable bargains aren't limited to celebrity-endorsed
brands like Kmart's Jaclyn Smith and Kathy Ireland collections, or
Wal-Mart's Kathie Lee Gifford line. The hip stuff runs the gamut
from no-name brands to discounters' private labels.
</P>
<P>
   Savvy bargain hunters say the key to finding chic looks on the
cheap is knowing the trends and selecting items that complement
your existing wardrobe.
</P>
<P>
   To demonstrate, we gave three style-conscious women a budget of
$100 each to scour the top three discount chains _ Target, Wal-Mart
and Kmart _ for the coolest summer merchandise on the racks. Here's
what they found:
</P>
<P>
   Georgia Lee, Southeast editor of Women's Wear Daily, on Target:
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's the very best of the discount stores. They have
been one of the leaders in giving the same trends you find in the
high-end stores for a good price. It's not going to last a
lifetime; but for a season, it's fine. If you're creative with the
accessories, you can make it look expensive.''
</P>
<P>
   Her top picks: A two-piece, bubble-gum pink bathing suit ($20.80
for the set). ``It's very reminiscent of Calvin Klein's, which go
for $80 to $90,'' said Lee. Also, there's a sheer, white pareo wrap
($9). ``They're very, very hot to wear over a swimsuit.''
</P>
<P>
   Patti Krohngold, restaurant/bar interior designer, on Kmart:
</P>
<P>
   ``I got a lot of bang for the buck,'' said Krohngold. ``You have
to dig deep, but if you go in with an open mind and keep abreast of
what's happening in fashion magazines you can find things. I can
take what Gucci's doing and go to Kmart.''
</P>
<P>
   Her top picks: A pair of black capri pants with fringe at the
bottom ($17.99). ``I'm 5-foot-10 and they were long enough,'' says
Krohngold, who has a hard time finding pants the length she needs.
</P>
<P>
   Also there was a boyish camp shirt by Route 66 ($9.99).
</P>
<P>
   ``The Route 66 is a good line of clothing. It's generic and
utilitarian.''
</P>
<P>
   C. Noel, free-lance fashion photographer, on Wal-Mart:
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know how well some of this is made, but it's cute. I
had to dig for the funkier stuff. They've got good accessories and
jewelry.''
</P>
<P>
   Her top picks: A white and red tank top with a Hostess logo
($6.87) and a red bandanna print halter ($12.97)
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to keep them,'' she said, ``especially the T-shirt!''
</P>
<P>
   Alma E. Hill writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
