the concept of a ``glass ceiling'' that limits women's career
advancement, and equates day care to leaving children ``in the care
of rented strangers.'' Don Willett, who recently went to England to
share Bush's ideas with conservative leaders there, also said in an
internal memo that efforts to improve working conditions for women
are nothing more than ``more
</P>
