   COX-NEWSPAPERS _ Cox Newspapers will buy two dailies in Ohio and
10 specialty publications. Gannett had planned to buy the papers as
part of a larger deal with Thomson but Cox had a right of first
refusal, and exercised it, for the papers its buying. (Bowman,
Dayton Daily News). 12.
</P>
<P>
   DEPOT-SCHOOLCOLORS _ University of Tennessee fans soon will be
able to find their true colors at Home Depot in what is being
billed as the first mass marketing of collegiate-coordinated paint.
Four Home Depot stores in Knoxville will start selling specially
licensed and formulated Tennessee Orange paint. If it goes over big
with fans, Carolina Blue, Notre Dame Gold, Ohio State Red and
Alabama Crimson may follow, Home Depot said. We'll ask when the
Georgia red will be on the market. (Bond, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 8.
