<P>
   CoxNet HEALTHY LIVING 0711: MEDICAL MYTHS _ Propelled by e-mail
and the Internet, hoaxes that prey on the anxieties of ordinary
people are proliferating as never before. They have become so
common, in fact, that the Atlanta-based Centers for Disease Control
and Prevention has introduced a page on its Web site to knock them
down. Art includes a 4-column color illustration of a comic book
cover with the subject being medical horrors. (Kicklighter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
