   OPEC-REVIEW (Undated) _ They mislead each other, although they
are supposedly on the same side. They make decisions that shape the
economies of the world based on disturbingly imperfect information.
The subject under discussion is not a failing Eastern European car
manufacturer, but the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries, or OPEC, the fractious group that controls the global
supply of crude oil, the commodity that runs the world. By Neela
Bannerjee.
