<P>
   PARIS-FASHIONS (Paris) _ Only 1,000, maybe 1,500 women are rich
enough, spoiled enough and otherwise bored enough to buy haute
couture clothes. But it is a very specific world, its influence and
entertainment value extending far beyond the thin women who sit
shank to shank along the gold-toned front row. By Cathy Horyn.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-RAVE (St. Petersburg) _ On the first weekend of July, as
many as 10,000 Russian youth laid siege to an abandoned and
crumbling Czarist structure some 30 miles off the coast of St.
Petersburg for dancing, performance art and general merriment
during the season of northern Russia's White Nights, when the sun
sets for only three hours. By John Varoli.
</P>
