<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Saturday, July 15 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   FLU-VACCINE (Los Angeles) _ There may be a shortage of influenza
vaccine this fall, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention
said Friday, in a year when federal officials are urging more
people to get the flu-fighting shot. The CDC, in response, is
asking local health departments and others to put off their typical
October flu shot campaigns until November. By Robert Monroe. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   RUCKUS-BOOTCAMP (Los Angeles) _ Starting Thursday, the Ruckus
Society holds a weeklong boot camp in Malibu, expected to bring 200
aspiring protesters to teach them how best to create chaos downtown
during the Democratic National Convention to draw attention to the
message behind the protest. By Jordan Smith. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   HOUSTON-SMOG (Los Angeles) _ Civic leaders want to clear the air
about Houston's label as the smoggiest city -- they've taken
another look at the data and say Los Angeles deserves the dishonor.
L.A. leaders obviously disagree. By Benjamin Parke. (Will move in
the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
