</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RUN-OLY-TRIALS0715-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Waller cruises into high jump final
 &HT;    By Mike Fish
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. _ For Tisha Waller, qualifying Friday in the
high jump proved a piece of cake. The Atlanta school teacher's
training partner, Lynn Houston, didn't have it quite so easy, but
she, too, advanced to Sunday's finals.
</P>
<P>
   Waller, reigning U.S. champion and an Atlanta Olympian, easily
cleared 5 feet, 10 3/4 inches in her first attempt. Houston
required a second attempt for clearance. But after just 25 minutes
of jumping at the single height at the U.S. Olympic Trials, the
field of 24 had been whittled in half for the finals.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm shocked it didn't take more attempts,'' said Waller, who
has a personal-best clearance of 6-7. ``I was hoping we'd get to
attempt two or three heights so I could get more work on the
(jumping) surface. I still have to make the team. Nothing is being
given to me.''
</P>
<P>
   It'll be an upset if Waller isn't Sydney-bound, however, with
her battling Amy Acuff and Gwen Wentland for the top spot. Houston
would be happy just to leave town having improved her personal-best
of 6-0 1/2.
</P>
<P>
   The 24-year-old is the younger sister of NBA star Allen Houston.
Next month, she'll complete the master's program in industrial
engineering at Georgia Tech. But her performance here will be the
test of whether she goes shopping for a real job or sticks with the
sport.
</P>
<P>
   It's generally assumed a clearance of at least 6-4 will be
required to make the team. That's the dream of Houston, whose
brother is attending a wedding in Detroit but called Friday to wish
her luck.
</P>
<P>
   As for her brother's game, Lynn said she dabbled with minimal
success on her high school basketball team. ``All I could do was
run fast and block shots,'' she said. ``I wasn't a scorer like
him.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
