to Jewish communities. (Rina Castelnuovo/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) GLEN ECHO, Md. -- July 14, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. JULY
16 -- CYRUS-MEHRI-PROFILE -- Cyrus Mehri, a lawyer who has
specialized in workplace discrimination cases, with his 4-year-old
son, Dylan in Glen Echo, Md.  Mehri filed a federal lawsuit against
the Coca-Cola Co. in April 1999, representing four black employees
who said they had been denied raises, promotions and other
advancement because of their race. The case against Coke was the
first for his law firm, Mehri, Malkin &AMP; Ross, which he opened in
September 1998. (Marty Katz/The New York Times)
</P>
