   (NYT6) NEW YORK -- July 14, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. JULY 16 --
INVEST-FRIEDMAN-MUTUAL -- The fund manager Robert L. Friedman with
his wife, Christine, and son, Thomas, in their rooftop garden in New
York. After years in the wilderness, value investing is staging a
comeback, and Friedman, who runs the $926.7 million Mutual European
fund, is basking in it. "These are good days for value investors," he
says. (Nicole Bengiveno/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) NEW YORK -- July 14, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. JULY 16 --
LARRY-DAVID-HBO -- Larry David, the co-creator and executive producer
of "Seinfeld" for seven years on the set of "Curb Your Enthusiasm,"
starting on HBO in October. David, who plays himself, is asked by an
old girlfriend to go with her to a support group for incest
